{
  "stem": "15694.10",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "The only thing, regret I had, is theirs was an open wagon.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And it was January.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] And the other wagons, at least, were closed.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "Little did I know that I had another guardian angel guiding me there.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "But that comes a bit later.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "Once I woke up, early morning, I looked at my left.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And my father was still asleep.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "I looked out, and it was like a giant shroud with people and valleys in between, valleys in between.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "It was an eerie view, like a cemetery, all corpses, nobody moved.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "Well, eventually, we got up.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "And throughout the snow, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] little did I know that people next door were licking this bit of snow, and it came into the crevices of the wider windows because they were dying of thirst and hunger.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "And when, where they started a train, a wagon full of people, sooner or later, as I described before, somebody got tired.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "The other sat on top of him, and it must have been terrible.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "And we were, according to that, we were going in luxury.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "Not only this, we actually had warm water.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "And for the first time, we gained great respect because we were the-- with our big menashkas, containing one litre and three litres, the man from the engine could pass us hot water.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "And we were given enough food, you know, for that, for the kapos and everything.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "We were in comparative luxury.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "But we were three weeks going probably for one camp to another, and nobody could take us.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "At one stage, practically between, well, middle of the journey, I saw one [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] sign on front, on top of me-- Prague, Prague.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "I remember the thoughts.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "No, today, nowadays, traveling is nothing.",
      "word_count": 6
    }
  ],
